{{Infobox power station | name = Crucey Solar Park | name_official = | image = | image_size = | image_caption = | image_alt = | location_map = France | location_map_size = | location_map_caption = | coordinates = {{coord|48|38|38|N|01|05|59|E|type:landmark|display=inline,title}} | coordinates_ref = | country = France | location = [[Chartres]] | status = o | construction_began = 2009 | commissioned = 2012 | decommissioned = | cost = | owner = [[EDF Énergies Nouvelles]] | operator = | solar_type = pv | ps_units_operational = 741,150 | ps_electrical_capacity = 60 [[Megawatt|MW]] | ps_electrical_cap_fac = | website = | extra = }} The '''Crucey Solar Park''' is a 60 MW solar farm in [[France]]. It was built by [[EDF Énergies Nouvelles]] in the communes of [[Maillebois]], [[Crucey-Villages]], and [[Louvilliers-lès-Perche]].<ref>{{Cite web|url = http://www.edf-energies-nouvelles.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/dp_centralepv_crucey_eng.pdf|title = The Crucey Photovoltaic Power Plant Press Kit|date = September 2012|accessdate = April 21, 2015|website = |publisher = |last = |first = }}</ref> It has 741,150 thin-film [[photovoltaics]] panels made by [[First Solar]].<ref>[http://www.gulfoilandgas.com/webpro1/MAIN/Mainnews.asp?id=23242 EDF Commissions 60 MWp Solar Plant in France]</ref><ref>[http://www.edf-energies-nouvelles.com/uploads/medias/1686/pr_crucey_280912_final_eng.pdf EDF Energies Nouvelles commissions a 60 MWp solar power plant in Crucey – France] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130228054417/http://www.edf-energies-nouvelles.com/uploads/medias/1686/pr_crucey_280912_final_eng.pdf |date=February 28, 2013 }}</ref> {{Clear}}
