{{Infobox journal | title = Journal of Electroanalytical Chemistry | cover = [[File:Journal_of_Electroanalytical_Chemistry_cover.gif]] | caption = | former_name = Journal of Electroanalytical Chemistry and Interfacial Electrochemistry | abbreviation = J. Electroanal. Chem. | discipline = [[Electrochemistry]] | peer-reviewed = | language = | editor = [[J. M. Feliu]] | publisher = [[Elsevier]] | country = | history = 1959&ndash;present | frequency = 24/year | openaccess = | license = | impact = 3.012 | impact-year = 2015 | ISSNlabel = | ISSN = 1572-6657 | eISSN = | CODEN = JECHES | JSTOR = | LCCN = | OCLC = | website = https://www.journals.elsevier.com/journal-of-electroanalytical-chemistry | link1 = http://www.sciencedirect.com/science/journal/15726657 | link1-name = Online access | link2 = <!-- up to |link5= --> | link2-name = <!-- up to |link5-name= --> | boxwidth = }} The '''''Journal of Electroanalytical Chemistry''''' is a [[peer review|peer-reviewed]] [[scientific journal]] on [[electroanalytical method|electroanalytical chemistry]], published by [[Elsevier]] twice per month. It was originally established in 1959 under the current name, but was known as the '''''Journal of Electroanalytical Chemistry and Interfacial Electrochemistry ''''' from 1967 to 1991. It is currently edited by [[J. M. Feliu]] ([[Universidad de Alicante]]). The journal is associated with the [[International Society of Electrochemistry]]. While the journal is now published exclusively in English, earlier volumes sometimes published articles in [[French language|French]] and [[German language|German]].
The journal, which ''[[The New York Times]]'' described as "a specialty publication not widely circulated" in 1990,<ref name="nyt"> <!-- The NYT mistakenly refers to the journal as "The Journal of Electroanalytic Chemistry"--> {{cite journal |first=William J. |last=Broad |date=October 30, 1990 |title=Cold Fusion Still Escapes Usual Checks Of Science |url=https://query.nytimes.com/gst/fullpage.html?res=9C0CEEDC1738F933A05753C1A966958260&sec=&spon=&pagewanted=2 |journal=[[New York Times]] }}</ref> became more broadly known in 1989 when [[Martin Fleischmann]] and [[Stanley Pons]] published a description of their controversial [[cold fusion]] research in it,<ref> {{cite journal |last1=Fleischmann |first1=Martin |last2=Pons |first2=Stanley |last3=Hawkins |first3=Marvin <!-- See errata --> |year=1989 |title=Electrochemically induced nuclear fusion of deuterium |journal=Journal of Electroanalytical Chemistry and Interfacial Electrochemistry |volume=261 |issue=2 |pages=301–308 |doi=10.1016/0022-0728(89)80006-3 }} (Erratum in {{cite journal |last1=<!-- --> |first1=<!-- --> |last2=<!-- --> |first2=<!-- --> |last3=<!-- --> |first3=<!-- --> |year=1989 |title=none |journal=Journal of Electroanalytical Chemistry and Interfacial Electrochemistry |volume=263 |issue=1 |pages=187–188 |doi=10.1016/0022-0728(89)80141-X }})</ref> withdrawing their work from publication in ''[[Nature (journal)|Nature]]'' after questions were raised during peer review there.<ref name="nyt" />
==Abstracting and indexing== According to the ''[[Journal Citation Reports]]'', the journal has a 2015 [[impact factor]] of 3.012.<ref name=WoS>{{cite book |year=2016 |chapter=Journal of Electroanalytical Chemistry |title=2015 [[Journal Citation Reports]] |publisher=[[Thomson Reuters]] |edition=Science |series=[[Web of Science]]}}</ref> It is [[abstracting and indexing|abstracted and indexed]] in the following [[bibliographic database]]s *[[Chemical Abstracts]] *[[Current Contents]] *[[Metals Abstracts]] *[[Engineering Index]] *[[INSPEC]] *[[World Aluminum Abstracts]] *[[Scopus]]
